
---


@startuml

abstract class ResearchGroup {
  +String id
  +String name
  +List<Researcher> researchers
}

class Department {
  +String id
  +String name
}

class Researcher {
  +String id
  +String name
  +String email
  +ResearchGroup currentGroup
  +List<WorkPackage> assignedWPs
}

class WorkPackage {
  +String id
  +String title
  +String description
  +ResearchGroup leaderGroup
  +List<Researcher> teamMembers
}

class Project {
  +String id
  +String title
  +String description
  +List<WorkPackage> workPackages
}

ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : belongsTo
Department "1" -- "0..*" ResearchGroup : contains
Researcher "1" -- "1" Project : assignedTo
Project "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : consistsOf
WorkPackage "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : hasTeamMember
WorkPackage "1" -- "1" ResearchGroup : ledBy

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Relationships:

- **`ResearchGroup`** is an abstract class that represents a group of researchers. It has a one-to-many relationship with `Researcher`.
- **`Department`** contains multiple `ResearchGroup`s.
- **`Researcher`** can be part of only one `ResearchGroup`, and may be assigned to multiple `WorkPackage`s.
- **`Project`** consists of multiple `WorkPackage`s.
- Each **`WorkPackage`** has exactly one **`ResearchGroup`** as its leader and can have multiple **`Researcher`** members.
- A **`Researcher`** can be assigned to any **`WorkPackage`**, regardless of which group leads it.
- When a **`Researcher`** changes groups or a **`WorkPackage`** leadership changes, the assignments are updated to reflect accurate service delivery tracking.

